-- Unitas Buys Carlyle’s Chinese Restaurant Chain for $40 Million
-- B y   C a t h y   C h a n
-- 2012-02-01T09:59:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-01/unitas-buys-carlyle-s-chinese-restaurant-chain-for-40-million.html
Unitas Capital Pte, the $4 billion
private equity firm, said it bought a stake in restaurant chain
Babela’s Group for $40 million from three minority shareholders.  Babela’s, which received an investment from  Carlyle Group
LP  in July 2007, owns an Italian dining brand with more than 120
outlets in Shanghai and Beijing as well as restaurants serving
Cantonese cuisine and Taiwanese desserts, Unitas said in a
statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cathy Chan in  Hong Kong  at 
 kchan14@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
